he strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:40:31.814000','2025-06-14 09:45:46.574000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(61,'o72w01m81844dts5uomgzji9','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development. The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads & bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:42:14.581000','2025-06-14 09:42:48.157000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(62,'o72w01m81844dts5uomgzji9','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A (Contract No. TP37/03)','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads & bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:42:14.581000','2025-06-03 12:42:14.581000','2025-06-03 12:42:14.625000',3,3,'en'),(63,'vqw3tn32frb4ngr1u9obqble','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:43:00.069000','2025-06-14 09:42:26.395000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(64,'vqw3tn32frb4ngr1u9obqble','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan (Contract No. ST 97/03)','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:43:00.069000','2025-06-03 12:43:00.069000','2025-06-03 12:43:00.122000',3,3,'en'),(65,'zoxj537nfeepkqe2b39vcu9h','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:43:56.629000','2025-06-14 09:43:39.219000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(67,'zoxj537nfeepkqe2b39vcu9h','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:43:56.629000','2025-06-03 12:45:15.399000','2025-06-03 12:45:15.476000',3,3,'en'),(68,'eu2zzdz3yagrlflcfeq1aw00','Mei Foo Station','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:45:58.724000','2025-06-14 09:44:02.909000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(69,'eu2zzdz3yagrlflcfeq1aw00','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:45:58.724000','2025-06-03 12:45:58.724000','2025-06-03 12:45:58.770000',3,3,'en'),(70,'verctnhswmb5bvk62cew84qt','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:46:35.725000','2025-06-14 09:46:08.590000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(72,'hydm274c79zguks4pnivagyb','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Works involved:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:47:24.610000','2025-06-14 09:43:15.022000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(73,'hydm274c79zguks4pnivagyb','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Works involved:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}]','2025-06-03 12:47:24.610000','2025-06-03 12:47:24.610000','2025-06-03 12:47:24.665000',3,3,'en'),(74,'xniapc50aw6abyjyxgbmio1v','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Highways Department','16 December 1998 - 31 March 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Widening of the section of Pok Fu Lam Road fronting Queen Mary Hospital involving the construction of new carriageway (partly on elevated structures) and reconstruction of existing carriageway; re-alignment of the upper section of Sassoon Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of the existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); construction of a link bridge linking the re-aligned Sassoon Road and the access road to Queen Mary Hospital; re-alignment of the upper section of Bisney Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); demolition of the existing footbridge across Pok Fu Lam Road and construction of a new footbridge at the same location; and associated drainage, landscaping, retaining walls and slope works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:48:32.710000','2025-06-14 09:44:56.355000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(75,'xniapc50aw6abyjyxgbmio1v','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road (Contract No. HY/98/10)','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Highways Department','16 December 1998 - 31 March 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Widening of the section of Pok Fu Lam Road fronting Queen Mary Hospital involving the construction of new carriageway (partly on elevated structures) and reconstruction of existing carriageway; re-alignment of the upper section of Sassoon Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of the existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); construction of a link bridge linking the re-aligned Sassoon Road and the access road to Queen Mary Hospital; re-alignment of the upper section of Bisney Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); demolition of the existing footbridge across Pok Fu Lam Road and construction of a new footbridge at the same location; and associated drainage, landscaping, retaining walls and slope works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:48:32.710000','2025-06-03 12:48:32.710000','2025-06-03 12:48:32.754000',3,3,'en'),(76,'zagoov2fawkpkao7lv50nco6','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Highways Department','01 September 1998 - 31 May 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Tuen Mun Road is a highway linking Tuen Mun and Kowloon. This project is to provide a climbing lane and hard shoulder to the existing Eastbound Carriageway of Tuen Mun Road Tai Lam Section and will in addition improve the slopes above Tuen Mun Road.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major challenge of the project is the cutting back of the slope, in rock, above the live traffic of Tuen Mun Road at the slope toe. In order to proceed with the excavation safely, the South Rock Knob was excavated, temporarily diverting both the eastbound and westbound traffic away from the north slope. The reinforced fill retaining wall along the existing median was also constructed ahead of any works at the northern slopes so that an additional traffic lane was provided for the temporary diversion of the traffic away from the northern slope. A temporary roadside rock fall fence was then erected at the slope toe with sand cushion behind to catch any blocks of rock that become detached and fall down the slope during excavation.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Another main feature of the project is the construction of the reinforced fill retaining wall at the Central Median for an extra traffic lane on top. This includes excavation at the existing slope of the Central median while temporarily supporting the existing eastbound carriageway (generally with pipe piles), erect precast concrete panels on the concrete footings and backfilling with selected fill materials sandwiched with galvanized steel reinforcing strips in layers. A temporary steel access bridge was constructed from the works area off Castle Peak Road, spanning across both the West bound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road and Castle Peak Road for the transportation of materials and plants to and from the site.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Throughout the project, the 3-lane traffic along the eastbound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road has to be maintained at all times. A complicated traffic diversion scheme was adopted to maintain the traffic flow for the full depth carriageway reconstruction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:49:42.979000','2025-06-14 09:45:22.923000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(78,'w8phckjj6bdi1awrc015veri','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km of water main of size up to 600mm diameter and associated works. These works included: a 450m long rectangular box culvert and a sea outfall; 4 nos. 6m high retaining wall; installation of 234m pavement soil nail and import of 300,000m³ filling material.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:51:34.494000','2025-06-14 09:47:50.626000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(80,'s38o0f43i0l7w575ld8xhxb0','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:52:32.188000','2025-06-14 09:50:04.234000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(81,'s38o0f43i0l7w575ld8xhxb0','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon (Contract No. SS E362)','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','[{\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The site formation includes a bulk excavation area of approximately 60,000m3. approximately 30% was rock excavation.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of 250m long retaining walls with maximum height of 12m.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of a 130m-long carriageway bridge on a slope.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of a single storey service building (43mx12mx3.7m high) with changing rooms, toilets, booking office, storage room, general office, first aid room, staff room, plant rooms, open court, seating area, kiosk and breezeway.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"External works comprising barrier walls, tennis courts, play area, jogging tracks, fitness stations, pavilion, pump rooms and fountains.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Landscaping works, car park, park furniture, drainage and plumbing works, M&E works, water filtration and circulation installation.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}]','2025-06-03 12:52:32.188000','2025-06-03 12:52:32.188000','2025-06-03 12:52:32.230000',3,3,'en'),(82,'f4u0ru7bw8dm9man2n8ai6rc','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:53:53.441000','2025-06-14 09:48:15.861000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(83,'f4u0ru7bw8dm9man2n8ai6rc','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun (TMTL 393)','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works. \", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:53:53.441000','2025-06-03 12:53:53.441000','2025-06-03 12:53:53.483000',3,3,'en'),(84,'k9m71j2te4nlv56iwtg7ciu5','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Works consisted of:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:54:46.677000','2025-06-14 09:48:41.114000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(85,'k9m71j2te4nlv56iwtg7ciu5','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works (Contract No. CV/95/14)','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The Works consisted of:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Excavation of some 500,000m3 of soil and rock\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Land filling of waste\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Drainage works and roadworks\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Site preparatory works\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}]','2025-06-03 12:54:46.677000','2025-06-03 12:54:46.677000','2025-06-03 12:54:46.728000',3,3,'en'),(86,'scb1mz5vpjlryqy36cdfv94u','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Port Works Division / Civil Engineering Department','01 September 1995 - 31 January 2000','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes the construction of 450m long vertical seawall, 1000m long sloping rubble seawall, 625m long 4-cells drainage culvert, roads, sewers, drains and watermains and reclamation of 28 hectares of land.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:55:36.462000','2025-06-14 09:47:00.159000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(88,'l8zxq8riybx1lgnm9cqg2hox','Ting Kau Bridge and Approach Viaducts','Ting Kau Bridge and Approach Viaducts','Highways Department','01 April 1995 - 31 January 1998','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The group was responsible for the bulk excavation work of the project. The most challenging part of the project was to maintain traffic flow on the busy Tuen Mun Road while excavating the adjacent high and steep rock slopes. Rock fall protective fences and meshes were erected along the toe of the slopes before excavation works commenced and various means of rock breaking including mechanical, chemical and blasting were engaged in order to proceed with the works safely. Rock blasting was organized at 12:00 noon and 01:00am to minimize disturbance to the public.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:56:25.673000','2025-06-14 09:47:23.925000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(90,'mtkskigoq0b4qjf48etk9vse','Formation of Po Lam Road Platform','Formation of Po Lam Road Platform','Civil Engineering Department','01 March 1995 - 15 March 1998','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"At the time of award, this contract was the first \\\"Design and Build\\\" site formation contract awarded by the Civil Engineering Department. The project includes the design and construction of the earthworks and associated road and drainage works for the formation of a platform in an area of 7 hectares; construction of a two-way road; investigation of the stability of existing slopes, retaining structures and land together with stabilisation works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:57:23.520000','2025-06-14 09:50:31.093000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(92,'xvcupf70wl2dhbt2lbgmkvej','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building','Lantau and Airport Railway Kowloon South Tunnels and Ancillary Building','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 November 1994 - 28 February 1998','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project, which forms part of the overall scheme for the Lantau and Airport Railway Link between the Western Immersed Tube and the new Kowloon Station, involves the construction of plant buildings and tunnels.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project consisted of:\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Associated drainage and access roads\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Ancillary building\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Architectural; finishes and cladding\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"landscaping\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}]','2025-06-03 12:59:10.244000','2025-06-14 09:49:11.751000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(94,'swak6ng5i40678rdc33y5m1b','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Territory Development Department','01 July 1994 - 31 January 1997','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The bridge was supported by two land abutments and six marine piers. Each abutment was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter land bored piles up to 56m long and each marine pier was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter marine piles.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The 1.5m diameter permanent linings of the marine bored piles were spliced into 24m to 30m lengths and pitched in position by piling barge.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:00:01.402000','2025-06-14 09:46:38.562000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(95,'swak6ng5i40678rdc33y5m1b','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure (Contract No. NL 2/93)','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Territory Development Department','01 July 1994 - 31 January 1997','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The bridge was supported by two land abutments and six marine piers. Each abutment was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter land bored piles up to 56m long and each marine pier was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter marine piles.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The 1.5m diameter permanent linings of the marine bored piles were spliced into 24m to 30m lengths and pitched in position by piling barge.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:00:01.402000','2025-06-03 13:00:01.402000','2025-06-03 13:00:01.447000',3,3,'en'),(96,'zrhi4utj6u4f051v6qezhut3','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road','Highways Department','01 May 1994 - 30 September 1996','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project includes alignment design and construction at four critical uphill sections (Ting Kau, Tai Lam, So Kwun Wat and Sam Shing Hui) of Tuen Mun Road, with a total length of 8.5km; geotechnical stabilisation on 31 cut slopes and 17 fill slopes; 6 retaining walls; structural reinforcement to six bridges, five underpasses and Sham Tseng Footbridge.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"During the construction, a restricted traffic diversion program was implemented to minimise construction disturbance to the public.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:00:56.133000','2025-06-14 09:49:42.037000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(98,'rf372a62t343z3rwhx5hj5r2','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment','China Resources Petroleum (Group) Company Limited','01 November 1993 - 01 July 1995','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project was the major civil work for the installation of the China Resources Petrochem Oil Terminal at Tsing Yi Island. The project involved the construction of a new tanker pier for 80,000 dwt fuel tankers, reclamation of 7 hectares of land by 2.8M cu.m of marine fill with substantial and stringent ground improvement works, dredging for reclamation and fairway realignment.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:01:44.275000','2025-06-14 09:51:08.077000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(99,'rf372a62t343z3rwhx5hj5r2','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment (CRPC South East Tsing Yi Oil Terminal Contract No. 3)','Site Formation, Tanker Pier and Fairway Realignment','China Resources Petroleum (Group) Company Limited','01 November 1993 - 01 July 1995','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The project was the major civil work for the installation of the China Resources Petrochem Oil Terminal at Tsing Yi Island. The project involved the construction of a new tanker pier for 80,000 dwt fuel tankers, reclamation of 7 hectares of land by 2.8M cu.m of marine fill with substantial and stringent ground improvement works, dredging for reclamation and fairway realignment.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:01:44.275000','2025-06-03 13:01:44.275000','2025-06-03 13:01:44.314000',3,3,'en'),(100,'fiio13qxkc081m84zqgi571m','Black Point Power Station Site Formation Work','Black Point Power Station Site Formation Work','Castle Peak Power Co. Ltd.','01 February 1993 - 28 February 1994','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The fill materials were graded before placement in order to control settlement and facilitate earlier piling and construction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Dredged marine mud was disposed at a designated site with the help of a Global Positioning Satellite (GPS) tracking system.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Blasting operation were carefully controlled to limit ground vibrations and avoid affecting concreting operations and a BBC broadcasting station nearby.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:02:45.604000','2025-06-14 09:52:16.674000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(102,'f6nwsk9k3tt90wc0js4pdjo0','North Lantau Expressway – Tai Ho Section','North Lantau Expressway – Tai Ho Section','Highways Department','01 August 1992 - 31 May 1996','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The contracted work of this project includes most of the earthwork and half of the seawall construction. All excavation and seawall construction had to be completed within 14 months to allow for subsequent construction activities. Excavated rock for the seawall construction was processed and sorted to meet the specifications of various rock types. Armour rock produced from excavation was insufficient which was then imported from the PRC to meet the programme requirement.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:03:18.062000','2025-06-14 09:51:31.337000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(103,'f6nwsk9k3tt90wc0js4pdjo0','North Lantau Expressway – Tai Ho Section (Contract No. HY/91/07)','North Lantau Expressway – Tai Ho Section','Highways Department','01 August 1992 - 31 May 1996','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The contracted work of this project includes most of the earthwork and half of the seawall construction. All excavation and seawall construction had to be completed within 14 months to allow for subsequent construction activities. Excavated rock for the seawall construction was processed and sorted to meet the specifications of various rock types. Armour rock produced from excavation was insufficient which was then imported from the PRC to meet the programme requirement.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:03:18.062000','2025-06-03 13:03:18.062000','2025-06-03 13:03:18.105000',3,3,'en'),(104,'x6u2a5kkawbtvbv8bbcdwq06','Construction of Yau Ma Tei Replacement Typhoon Shelter Phase II and Jordan Road Reclamation Phase I','Construction of Yau Ma Tei Replacement Typhoon Shelter Phase II and Jordan Road Reclamation Phase I','Civil Engineering Department','01 April 1991 - 31 August 1993','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes dredging of 34 million m3 of marine mud, formation of 75 ha of reclaimed land using marine sand, construction of a public cargo working area, seawall, underground pump houses and associated road and drainage works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project brought together a formidable fleet of dredgers, including trailing suction hopper, cutter suction and large grab dredgers.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"A total of 9,700 concrete blocks, each weighing about 20 tonnes, were made by the company at its precasting yard in Tsuen Wan and shipped in by Derrick Lighter for construction of the vertical seawall.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"As Hong Kong is one of the busiest ports in the world, the crewmen on board the dredgers had to be especially vigilant to avoid the constant flow of ships, both day and night.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:03:59.591000','2025-06-14 09:51:52.884000',NULL,3,20,'en'),(105,'x6u2a5kkawbtvbv8bbcdwq06','Construction of Yau Ma Tei Replacement Typhoon Shelter Phase II and Jordan Road Reclamation Phase I','Construction of Yau Ma Tei Replacement Typhoon Shelter Phase II and Jordan Road Reclamation Phase I','Civil Engineering Department','01 April 1991 - 31 August 1993','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project includes dredging of 34 million m3 of marine mud, formation of 75 ha of reclaimed land using marine sand,  construction of a public cargo working area, seawall, underground pump houses and associated road and drainage works.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"This project brought together a formidable fleet of dredgers, including trailing suction hopper, cutter suction and large grab dredgers.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"A total of 9,700 concrete blocks, each weighing about 20 tonnes, were made by the company at its precasting yard in Tsuen Wan and shipped in by Derrick Lighter for construction of the vertical seawall.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"As Hong Kong is one of the busiest ports in the world, the crewmen on board the dredgers had to be especially vigilant to avoid the constant flow of ships, both day and night.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 13:03:59.591000','2025-06-03 13:03:59.591000','2025-06-03 13:03:59.690000',3,3,'en'),(106,'fmcfbgqr0wqydlswrcmi9oyg','南丫岛发电厂4号及5号 FGD设备翻新工程','南丫岛发电厂4号及5号 FGD设备翻新工程','香港电灯有限公司','2006 年 12 月 22 日 - 2008 年 05 月 26 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:26:32.959000','2025-06-14 10:14:20.152000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(108,'vol48vaxnwhxlc7eb2u0bt5q','屯门第38区环保园发展工程','屯门第38区环保园发展工程','环境保护署','2006 年 07 月 03 日 - 2010 年 01 月 01 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"环保园是一个关键因素的战略，其目的是促进本地循环再造业和快速激活一个可持续发展的经济提供长期的土地设施的环境及循环再造业。通过鼓励和促进再利用，回收和循环再造的废物资源，并返回他们的消费循环中，环保园将有助于利用的潜力本地循环再造业，减轻沉重的需求，香港的堆填区。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"环保园占地 20公顷的土地位于屯门第38区，将分两个阶段发展。环保园第一期（约 8公顷），将用于对结束占领和2006年第二期（约 12公顷）在2009年。各种环保设施正在使用首次在香港，如太阳管道，太阳能水龙头，并且有绿色屋顶等等\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:27:34.450000','2025-06-14 10:13:17.892000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(110,'o7g6euwy408sxs0j15fg8s8j','白石角发展计划基础设施工程 - 第 2A 阶段','白石角发展计划基础设施工程 - 第 2A 阶段','土木工程拓展署','2004 年 06 月 29 日 - 2008 年 10 月 15 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"白石角发展计划基础设施工程 主要工程项目包括地盘平整工程，以及道路和桥梁建设，自行车道，海滨长廊，人行隧道，及相关的环境美化工程等\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:29:10.164000','2025-06-14 10:11:47.146000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(112,'y8prmiqjyiy8js4ix7nr23h0','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山','拓展署','2004 年 03 月 26 日 - 2006 年 11 月 18 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"项目包括沙田及马鞍山区内土木工程项目并特别针对于斜坡，道路及渠务工程。由于涉及交通不便的地区，我们采用了崭新的施工方法。 如在多石村后山山上建造一条120米长围栏，我们利用了直升机运送围栏组件到现场及使用特殊设计滑轮系统利用人力安装整个围栏。在修葺2公里长马鞍山海滨长廊时，我们利用陆地及海上机械设备来运输及放置防波堤石。避免对邻近海堤附近的居民做成滋扰，我们在施工过程中应用不同环境的预防措施及与市民建立良好的沟通系统。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:30:02.360000','2025-06-14 10:12:25.050000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(114,'kav8yc8a4ji834ngasr5xp11','昂坪污水处理厂，污水干渠及污水排放管道','昂坪污水处理厂，污水干渠及污水排放管道','渠务署','2003 年 08 月 18 日 - 2006 年 03 月 09 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"前往工地的信道一直为整个项目的最大挑战。由于限制车辆使用东涌道，本项目取得的许可证甚少。同时，因最接近工地的混凝土厂也需要超过一小时的车程，所以，每天混凝土的浇注量，只能限于200立方米。这限制对于工程的进度起了很大的影响。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"污水处理厂内的各座钢筋混凝土结构及建筑物，都呈不规则的形状。因此，虽耍采用特别设计的模板及复杂的临时支撜结构。这也为整个项目带来一定的难度。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:31:10.581000','2025-06-14 10:12:47.411000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(116,'k5tyzhrz3wx4ihs4kuoud9ur','美孚站','美孚站','九广铁路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"美孚站位于荔枝角公园内，采用密封式设计。其设计特色在于使车站与公园环境融为一体。车站的天台设计为空中花园，其中包括园林绿化及各种休闲设施，为邻近的大型高密度住宅区如美孚新村及清丽苑等的居民提供服务。本站的整体设计及建造，均以融入相邻居民区与环境为主题。例如：提供足够的人行道及车道从车站通往邻近的住宅区等。在建筑期间减低对居民的影响，也是一个重要的事项。所以，在建筑期间，专门修建了一条临时人行天桥横跨整个工地，为居民提供方便的来往通道。工程完成后，由于西铁的通车，美孚站及其天台上的空中花园的建成启用，大幅改善了邻近地区的交通及环境，居民的生活质素也得到相应提高。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:32:03.922000','2025-06-14 10:11:23.915000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(118,'eqtg9ms4e8z2nqp7n729zxzr','土木及基础工程','土木及基础工程','九广铁路','1999 年 07 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"该合约包括西铁车厂及锦田站的建造、安装，土木及基建的设计。该工程包括所有地盘平整、渠务、道路、公用设施、环境美化、主要排水渠道及轨道路基平整工程。这些道路工程包括兴建一条约660米长的双程高架桥横跨地盘、消防通道和公共通道、停车场及道路交汇处设施。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:33:09.371000','2025-06-14 10:13:59.941000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(119,'eqtg9ms4e8z2nqp7n729zxzr','土木及基础工程 (九广铁路西铁合约编号CC-601)','土木及基础工程','九广铁路','1999 年 07 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"该合约包括西铁车厂及锦田站的建造、安装，土木及基建的设计。该工程包括所有地盘平整、渠务、道路、公用设施、环境美化、主要排水渠道及轨道路基平整工程。这些道路工程包括兴建一条约660米长的双程高架桥横跨地盘、消防通道和公共通道、停车场及道路交汇处设施。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:33:09.371000','2025-06-04 01:33:09.371000','2025-06-04 01:33:09.427000',8,8,'zh-CN'),(120,'fa7ez42hbh08ugv1eut1nkrz','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期','土木工程署','1998 年 12 月 30 日 - 2002 年 05 月 17 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"工程包括建造700米长的斜坡式防波海堤。管理位于沙田47B区的公众填土趸船转运站。收集公众填料。在白石角填海17公顷土地及进行相关的土质处理。建造单孔箱形暗渠，进行环境监察及绿化工程。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:34:08.034000','2025-06-14 10:12:06.193000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(122,'zr3ru3c6akfzjytwp8fc6yfe','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"本项目的重点为扩阔一段在全港规模最大，最主要的玛丽医院前的薄扶林道与及改善其邻近的路口，提供一个畅通无阻的交汇处。确保紧急车辆能够尽快进出医院，也改善附近一带地区的交通流量。在扩阔薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行车道。同时，也包括把现有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。并重建沙孙道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本项目也包括以重建的沙孙道为起点，建造一条连接玛丽医院的连接桥。重建班士尼道与薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是于斜坡上兴建的高架行车道。由于大部份的高架行车道的结构工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上进行，工程的难度大大的提高。尤其是在进行基础工程的阶段。为建造现浇搅拌桩承建商采用了大规模的临时工作台及在斜坡上开挖的临时平台。薄扶林道为连接港岛西区及南区的其中一条主要通道，交通流量非常高，车速又快。于工程进行期间，为确保交通安全及畅顺，承建商提供了大量的相关操施，包括：建造临时扩阔路面，提供及安装大量的交通标置，指示及照明系统等。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:35:01.080000','2025-06-14 10:11:02.656000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(124,'odjvfp12xdlkfd4n4wxz015s','屯门公路改善工程 – 大榄段','屯门公路改善工程 – 大榄段','路政署','1998 年 09 月 01 日 - 2001 年 05 月 31 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"屯门公路是連接屯门和九龍的主要道路。这项工程旨在为屯门公路大榄段现有的东行车道提供一条爬坡车道和硬路肩 ，并改善屯门公路上的斜坡。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"本项目的其中一个重点为于屯门公路北侧之岩石斜坡上进行开挖。为使开挖能安全地进行，不至影向斜坡下繁忙的交通，我司把公路南侧邻近兄弟桥的山坡削平，建造临时车道，把屯门公路东、西向的行车线南移，远离开挖进行的工地。同时，我司又调动施工的次序，先于分隔东西行车线的路中斜坡上，建造强化填料护土墙及新增的永久行车线，把东行的行车线南移，远离北面的斜坡，腾出空间，于路旁建造临时防滚石网及铺设沙软垫，以防止于斜坡开挖时松脱的石块，滚下斜坡，对路过的车辆构成危险。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"项目的另一重点为于分隔东西行车线的路中斜坡上设计及建造强化填料护土墙以兴建一条新增的永久行车线。建造该段强化填料护土墙包括于斜坡上进行开挖。开挖期间，以临时迷你桩墙枝撑东行车道的路基。建造护土墙的工序包括浇注钢筋混凝土地基，于地基上按装预制钢筋混凝土构件，于构件背后分层回填、压实及按装特别填料及经热浸镀锌处理的钢制强化筋。为进行此部份之工程，我司特别设计及建造了一条钢结构临时桥，从青山公路旁的工地至位于分隔屯门公路东西行线的路中斜坡的工地，横跨青山公路及屯门公路西行线，以便运送材料、机械、工具及人员行返工地。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"在整个项目进行过程中，要碓保屯门公路东行之三条行车线畅通无阻。为进行重建现有的路面，我司设计及执行了一个极为复杂、多阶段的逐行车线交通改道计划。重建路面得以顺利完成，并没有对交通构成重大影向。\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:35:58.590000','2025-06-14 10:13:38.861000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(126,'t7csvy76dx4zujvu3sqzllxq','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程','拓展署','1998 年 03 月 18 日 - 2003 年 05 月 05 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"建造长1.6公里的主干道和长7.3公里直径600厘米的水管及相关工程。这些工程包括：\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-04 01:36:57.173000','2025-06-14 10:17:28.333000',NULL,8,20,'zh-CN'),(127,'t7csvy76dx4zujvu3sqzllxq','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程 (合约编号：TP28/95)','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程','拓展署','1998 年 03 月 18 日 - 2003 年 05 月 05 日','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"建造长1.6公里的主干道和长7.3公里直径600厘米的水管及相关工程。这些工程包括：\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"450米长的矩形地下渠及排出海港排水口一个\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unordered\", \"children\": [{\"type\": \"list-item\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"6 米高的护土墙4幅\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]}, {\"type\": \"list\", \"format\": \"unorde