06-03 12:40:31.814000','2025-06-06 16:25:13.282000','2025-06-06 16:25:13.343000',3,16,'en'),(234,'verctnhswmb5bvk62cew84qt','Civil and Infrastructure Works (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-601)','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities. \", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:46:35.725000','2025-06-06 16:25:30.471000','2025-06-06 16:25:30.526000',3,16,'en'),(235,'zagoov2fawkpkao7lv50nco6','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section (Contract No. HY/98/01)','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Highways Department','01 September 1998 - 31 May 2001','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Tuen Mun Road is a highway linking Tuen Mun and Kowloon. This project is to provide a climbing lane and hard shoulder to the existing Eastbound Carriageway of Tuen Mun Road Tai Lam Section and will in addition improve the slopes above Tuen Mun Road.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"The major challenge of the project is the cutting back of the slope, in rock, above the live traffic of Tuen Mun Road at the slope toe. In order to proceed with the excavation safely, the South Rock Knob was excavated, temporarily diverting both the eastbound and westbound traffic away from the north slope. The reinforced fill retaining wall along the existing median was also constructed ahead of any works at the northern slopes so that an additional traffic lane was provided for the temporary diversion of the traffic away from the northern slope. A temporary roadside rock fall fence was then erected at the slope toe with sand cushion behind to catch any blocks of rock that become detached and fall down the slope during excavation.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Another main feature of the project is the construction of the reinforced fill retaining wall at the Central Median for an extra traffic lane on top. This includes excavation at the existing slope of the Central median while temporarily supporting the existing eastbound carriageway (generally with pipe piles), erect precast concrete panels on the concrete footings and backfilling with selected fill materials sandwiched with galvanized steel reinforcing strips in layers. A temporary steel access bridge was constructed from the works area off Castle Peak Road, spanning across both the West bound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road and Castle Peak Road for the transportation of materials and plants to and from the site.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}, {\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Throughout the project, the 3-lane traffic along the eastbound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road has to be maintained at all times. A complicated traffic diversion scheme was adopted to maintain the traffic flow for the full depth carriageway reconstruction.\", \"type\": \"text\"}]}]','2025-06-03 12:49:42.979000','2025-06-06 16:25:44.725000','2025-06-06 16:25:44.781000',3,16,'en'),(236,'w8phckjj6bdi1awrc015veri','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I (Contract No. TP28/95)','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','[{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"children\": [{\"text\": \"Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km o